title: A systematic study of (n,7Be) reactions on medium and heavy mass nuclei indiced by 53 MeV d(Be)-Breakup neuterons

x4freetext: A systematic study of (n,7Be) reactions on medium and
heavy mass nuclei indiced by 53 MeV d(Be)-Breakup
The 53 MeV deuteron beam impinging on a 1 cm
thick water-cooled Be disc produced breakup neuterons
which were very strongly forward peaked.
The elements to be irradiated were packed between Al
monitor foils. The thickness of each packing
containing several elements was kept between 0.8 and
effective at the irradiated sample was determined via
27Al(n,a) monitor reaction, the excitation function of
which is known well up to 28 MeV.
